{
  "_id": "fhSubWyrmiron001",
  "name": "Wyrmiron Salts",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubFantasy0001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Black flakes ground from rust-stained scales shed by elder dragons. Inhaled through a snuff horn, the salts coat the lungs in a brief, glittering ash. Mercenaries pay handsomely; clerics call it desecration.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 10 minutes you gain a +1 bonus to AC as your skin hardens with a faint scaly sheen.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Wyrmiron Salts (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Wyrmiron Salts.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks (your skin makes a faint metallic rasp).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 4.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(4 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Snuff Horn.</em></p>"
    },
